const e=[{level:1,title:"STRATEGIC DOSSIER: Captain Morgan (Diageo)",content:`
`},{level:2,title:"A Note on Method",content:`
This strategic dossier is compiled from a set of verified findings. Each claim has been rigorously assessed for corroboration across multiple independent sources. Claims supported by at least two distinct sources are marked "corroborated." Claims supported by only one source are marked "[single-source]." Claims that could not be verified due to inaccessible sources, future-dated information, or speculative content are marked "unverifiable" and excluded from the main body of the dossier, though their original status and note are retained in the raw findings for transparency. Conflicting claims are presented with their respective values and sources, highlighting the discrepancy. All figures are cited with their full source URLs inline. This methodology ensures the highest possible accuracy and reliability for strategic decision-decision-making.

`},{level:2,title:"1. History",content:`
The Captain Morgan brand is named after the 17th-century Welsh privateer Sir Henry Morgan (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFR0FKwS9GjGFa4PvhPrQVfD8HSpQREFoZ509Tmq9XV1VlKQmFpc4elrW_U0sy4dZOIS8sxOai2vILmTz87GZ_ntIdfRV59Rro6FNQhjvr5P2S0m9E7xW1lpFh_PI1MDbCF3LIiSA=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGVatqMmmLJwavwYt314Lz1ph5S73aXjxsI-KLlNJaecSU2Q6sfXmGFNCUy9JfU0d9wcgFEtAEmJYavDOA7Yxb1_KSnQFlDdM90qopVjW-flxL3jcnRzgPVKFRrHeMYPnN_bFASRKQYqOyL9MUjH2w=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE33Tk3YkfM1UWuLwr4pIZ5hqKDlN4FnCdxC6KOrtulrPBhQLGjyOuV2RbY-ROCjyQcarKbaaj61sywtu7JQJBkJQcwt4udElxBARP6dKjkrzmyPonlxeeLdX7FKWGBOb3uWhouyDfglmWaIM9GO67jEsrs6kmzlDgPRz-yqyTWyacOMRFQ8jMt). It was founded in 1944 by the Seagram Company in Jamaica (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFR0FKwS9GjGFa4PvhPrQVfD8HSpQREFoZ509Tmq9XV1VlKQmFpc4elrW_U0sy4dZOIS8sxOai2vILmTz87GZ_ntIdfRV59Rro6FNQhjvr5P2S0m9E7xW1lpFh_PI1MDbCF3LIiSA=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGCilUS58J_gK3ZqhMUOy76zKetCayZdHtvRJeooXFLB_Spn2xp5cR4VfbrZNW-UdMwmCkeMwJpMimKKYD0FNfZXCxDEltrtxnL3DEYV0vOt-Fhshqw_Ymji3GTFPQ9yP2u-fRD7bMNJqpi8cfxVbU6BNDj8K51BYIqbcErYcu6L3UeMVcpwLmjcQbDQsPuv2sIRaBp1E=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHsrxhlRCnl_SK9zg4zJDy0ZJtdI1rS7Kjrwb0IRZqtWaT7E47Nrwry8sPWJRlkV-n_FA-ezmkvt4-DAYo0d9khDBGQal5JdoYzEQUuQ8LYDNcGez46GI0r0u9JP_NXBd0XpMhgJNKdKqcydXwqTrjCQNnlSWhpQ40TxprOb05yJdSRyarKXy261yDlWc76l8KsYAqjJjFazyH_I-d03uFSumIFAX7QpJTqap3uVSxO3TAmQM_bXOYULugcykdcIu4jgOq). Seagram's CEO, Samuel Bronfman, acquired the rights to a spiced rum recipe from a local Jamaican pharmacy, which led to the commercial production of Captain Morgan rum (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFR0FKwS9GjGFa4PvhPrQVfD8HSpQREFoZ509Tmq9XV1VlKQmFpc4elrW_U0sy4dZOIS8sxOai2vILmTz87GZ_ntIdfRV59Rro6FNQhjvr5P2S0m9E7xW1lpFh_PI1MDbCF3LIiSA=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGCilUS58J_gK3ZqhMUOy76zKetCayZdHtvRJeooXFLB_Spn2xp5cR4VfbrZNW-UdMwmCkeMwJpMimKKYD0FNfZXCxDEltrtxnL3DEYV0vOt-Fhshqw_Ymji3GTFPQ9yP2u-fRD7bMNJqpi8cfxVbU6BNDj8K51BYIqbcErYcu6L3UeMVcpwLmjcQbDQsPuv2sIRaBp1E=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHsrxhlRCnl_SK9zg4zJDy0ZJtdI1rS7Kjrwb0IRZqtWaT7E47Nrwry8sPWJRlkV-n_FA-ezmkvt4-DAYo0d9khDBGQal5JdoYzEQUuQ8LYDNcGez46GI0r0u9JP_NXBd0XpMhgJNKdKqcydXwqTrjCQNnlSWhpQ40TxprOb05yJdSRyarKXy261yDlWc76l8KsYAqjJjFazyH_I-d03uFSumIFAX7QpJTqap3uVSxO3TAmQM_bXOYULugcykdcIu4jgOq). The original spiced rum recipe was created for medicinal purposes by a Kingston pharmacy (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHLh4lHayzgOXjxREoBWDxsRwylHrz-F-W1gBDIYkjyigjXcfKtc2aeBbOyjc9eEYaS94hL4uwlHLqdEwuwpfM13k_Vz08le09CBS-6MVTlMD8pkjG3ocWYkkNFNIqoC1aWhpAhn6HO3xYQF15-9zfvxm8ABK0kkh6wLEs7Ngugue7eyFCrjV6GuKtMtpP2se4Y9vo=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEqTlGbtQoV3d3UaJHxeNrwR5tk9HC0WIp6hzzY00-kDGS8uPV3q1ew9v2GCoXvj5-KzxEw0CUaS1fYC6nn6mBPBOTTSnIApz87hAsMo4lOv78QL5ysCk-Ga5qmgcGitOpvV3tZAX9dLchdVX5fiQi-PA=).

Captain Morgan Original Spiced Rum was first introduced to the United States in 1984 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFR0FKwS9GjGFa4PvhPrQVfD8HSpQREFoZ509Tmq9XV1VlKQmFpc4elrW_U0sy4dZOIS8sxOai2vILmTz87GZ_ntIdfRV59Rro6FNQhjvr5P2S0m9E7xW1lpFh_PI1MDbCF3LIiSA=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGVatqMmmLJwavwYt314Lz1ph5S73aXjxsI-KLlNJaecSU2Q6sfXmGFNCUy9JfU0d9wcgFEtAEmJYavDOA7Yxb1_KSnQFlDdM90qopVjW-flxL3jcnRzgPVKFRrHeMYPnN_bFASRKQYqOyL9MUjH2w=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGjRAKzTVfo6g0bLD6C2xhZVYsJgj5NkRS2-jDx4x1JPabGBPL6o-oZDi21DTKMHyvFw-Gr8VmRSWIn91T-WjjxoqidomozainQDjITmsSQwMGob3xsUEpcqB9SisSNm-YGLMw9DFKmvFshZA=). The iconic pirate mascot was created in the early 1980s by artist Don Maitz (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFR0FKwS9GjGFa4PvhPrQVfD8HSpQREFoZ509Tmq9XV1VlKQmFpc4elrW_U0sy4dZOIS8sxOai2vILmTz87GZ_ntIdfRV59Rro6FNQhjvr5P2S0m9E7xW1lpFh_PI1MDbCF3LIiSA=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGNZ3Faq7CCpDEnRpIBhe-RVSnmSEjnn4vTWQONbUckAt5p19-G_rPxi9CLYswOCYc3vMXegYmCWXszfvLuFc2tjTYdbjnKZ1DsEMoFqOty4Pz1gJlquAHUlJXnKQNOVOy_7OwtIIwGIzibtE7AOEB_EHQVG5D24Z1Vfyqb6KfLeTVNDViW54sd3ZfEGT1Yy-Q=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHVJGdyOirDKuUuflyJuXnVZzZY5hL1eT_-WgajMT7VkCgF_QkcPjegy8AZo9Y2Vyd2VMTlQrUotJ_JEnhRP5mVluQdxd04X_LTTE6-cPh4olz7_Zpn3RMRx6nH5_7AAybypHTab-7ymDAq6_doQdxRy6K0XzShCn-kyMw=).

In April 2023, Captain Morgan rolled out a global redesign of its packaging and reformulated its Original Spiced Rum to include Madagascar vanilla (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGwtWlBWApKIrXyT9Fyesbyx3cAW-yUeCzCGAQpSqefyClVPJiRtVaTmtrKH9nrlsl6GPqgTkYYsm2yO6xEPX_POLUFVb5HR4n7Lo29fsW56uT5m9QShbBGRTw4DF-66Mr-wXAX8SZitUOSEBFWgtaK-TmxxTDPelA9qnBw-BR0lrpYktjMuZi665rYOVd4JOt7uJuA=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFRWh1P6788epYnx5o5gwoKDVkLlaRTLAm7ccyKaWEuY9xDPSbLPg_SBCi1Hae2ggTb6fH21qQGn6sV2UAxBJijbpMlPrbbAVdrZjpe9z-RZzHNoJH9tvjCAJBd0Iv_JYw7N4VivnPuQB3rIO3dmxjy1md9ZSktd9wiQGndnETt61OOXHaHnfW1zDEBnuXn_4UkbA=). This recipe update aimed to 'spice it up' and highlight the brand's 'elevated liquid' (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEB4JG51OePmPkyJpr5qb2iwdiSKDuRO2hMefJVD0pFTnLWjbJ9UZLMtcIyt9u38YF10ySjyrrxjPJivSsZgU5y9s0gw4qn8zOCRnRTYZ_D7x15HSBVWaBOhIpJnm_WqE6RNh2aAHjVQX-IvfCWjPzbMgsJgd6ZREUbJ6D4h4IfRXGdJESCkl2YZ8rSAF4sH0B5gf0).

`},{level:2,title:"2. Ownership",content:`
Captain Morgan was originally established by the Seagram Company in 1944 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEPNTFY21wkofOM0GXeH8ouQHw5pIUx2DIa2iSklpz-NKoQDZG5ElpkDsdlF_Xl-c787szODrL0G_sIOFw5EzELOCjECXXiS85kARCOk-DEQYCANrnzl3JZuI_clnJ6ESf8dmSn6piVkHre2YfSwLLAX, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEelFkRswg0RBIx8Kf0b30bd6oY4lbMb-_8yhi_pSoZ_KwFFnWWZyKRpHUspt5cScuOjJkg7PHApmiUD72u_WWZgKVY5k_nCjwe5jF4XlSuh-l4koyQPEGFXSBjMqD65o8xRGXWnxIjBCkv8a0=). In 2001, Diageo acquired Captain Morgan as part of a larger joint acquisition of Seagram's Spirits and Wine business (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFWyVOxepg65CUQejX6nBvSt5lTSj_q0ezOmGJei_hGbky9nFAMr1uoQxPjgqdGSrG2N6OEfz3Vvwd8mUx-zcwi25DedWbabu7OCx82o3NlbV00tO3ypkLTz7_-KQM5dGsUzlgFrP4n, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE0XzkxOx1a5pWDBCSOtEiIJiirE_UZ-ZxnHzl58MuzK4FqzoQ8RRWhuI2_hD1snszDkThFEuYVdIMDkjjlhDYFdkEs5LGZnd_6NJlVH2eNdORQwgo_gqq3Py4-zTKDYeXVo1tA3ExOHLsh9TCsg1Xof33tZQi78mEfZM2rsCOZfwk7SbpMEU9nnyyb_MIjLpW2JkKBQ6d8tRDeCM-vAeUIw==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGBBcZkI9eWGy5eMC2vvbrzBW2chZt7ujxYfoVAeNuu1WK6OWYqSX6ybCTVemRr8Lhjmduwq48lr_IbDmAooRPYgSJIYHCQoE5DOi9yylL8wuqZN_XJIjf11FnogHi_dn73Ym5kstZVbw==). The total acquisition of Seagram's Spirits and Wine business by Diageo and Pernod Ricard was valued at US$8.15 billion (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE0XzkxOx1a5pWDBCSOtEiIJiirE_UZ-ZxnHzl58MuzK4FqzoQ8RRWhuI2_hD1snszDkThFEuYVdIMDkjjlhDYFdkEs5LGZnd_6NJlVH2eNdORQwgo_gqq3Py4-zTKDYeXVo1tA3ExOHLsh9TCsg1Xof33tZQi78mEfZM2rsCOZfwk7SbpMEU9nnyyb_MIjLpW2JkKBQ6d8tRDeCM-vAeUIw==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEWp_kjLt5TAN9fs1dBx4CY3v_2fhoc25eyUxy6RG_QP53CJTWpdyo3KGcyDpK4I5XHKWsMoHRjBAPi2zlFxA2mQ9iFLbVV4KP1TOpwzsCRXxZY5mYrX5-g3MeGl4VZ6lZfhTW4Mtn12jFOJ5MelrZNirC2yqp5ps4UmFMxmEx6klrJTcdv44cH3Drg, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFfUhBfRDb-8C7tGzb-kxoNYATKUDIInjWh_H82kmAMByc3L2M_NaMk8GV_15t-F1ZQV_wFtez_E00JYS4pcLuPEAnR8NFLGYg5W4wi6f_mfgRd1OBUh2pNNAQS67jJ7WpyV_1eG8ShJtbGBnY8y2bOxcGB5rpDlChyaGrGexrsp3V4UjhhyOOfLasEM2jad7LXJfE2shcxMQ==). Diageo's share of this acquisition was US$5 billion (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFWyVOxepg65CUQejX6nBvSt5lTSj_q0ezOmGJei_hGbky9nFAMr1uoQxPjgqdGSrG2N6OEfz3Vvwd8mUx-zcwi25DedWbabu7OCx82o3NlbV00tO3ypkLTz7_-KQM5dGsUzlgFrP4n, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEOhxVoLWhC29i3zze_AI6QHMhzQEiywd4SbpRExjS_nfoEye7_7FShheNfZaK0hQtv4byxWrDqu3a4r1MMGvT8bmXi2O9fljsvaC-n47i6mcoRZIqd6f_TB7YUrNIkFwA0H6MyhKj-acc_coAd). The acquisition faced U.S. Federal Trade Commission (FTC) scrutiny, which led Diageo to divest its Malibu rum brand (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHz2XI_82dAL9oCGvm9TF5az4pifvrKSesgXLA8YQgOj4rfCwNXS5uY2fdF4QRHpY4ieHQ-UCU_eQjVpKpzUH1pEYfPdlzfyrOdb2vkwintllgQRqAldSulMysFsnf1sVgf0WmMhqMjdPmfqn-s44Ro2GH0G_twAt1vbul7ESnowY6p_j657X4-qJ2NMrm9n670-c6y4r3t8QC4zpvXI_L3Xd4kBNjVhghvzguNTrPQobLSOQ0mQzyi8RJxRl4Qg3lKdKV4EtzzOowKSqJMFyifNY=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFWyVOxepg65CUQejX6nBvSt5lTSj_q0ezOmGJei_hGbky9nFAMr1uoQxPjgqdGSrG2N6OEfz3Vvwd8mUx-zcwi25DedWbabu7OCx82o3NlbV00tO3ypkLTz7_-KQM5dGsUzlgFrP4n).

Captain Morgan is owned by Diageo globally, excluding Jamaica [single-source] (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQENX3nHkZMYB2ojWLu0VfDW86Goo3kTPbkSMuViYREWI_o477N7NlPnppswjXBNN4IGNKvwW7HJ95yc_gAs91OAq4Arp1QP42fUYhQSaE07waW8ffuXtzCxhOrc5MAcuVSO8FNdIy1g==). This fragmented ownership, while historically rooted, presents potential complexities for global brand messaging and supply chain integration, particularly if the Jamaican market's preferences or regulatory environment diverge significantly from Diageo's global strategy. Diageo does not own the Captain Morgan trademark in Jamaica, where J. Wray & Nephew Ltd. (Campari Group) produces a separate Captain Morgan rum for local consumption (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXMY3ZA0h_BIsuYJAfXsrPUNGcFVtdTtY6iwerIaFAG2cANwTvY5S7xQzBIVwP-XKa0FB34EQjjnSA78r397pGpMDR71pfuLhO7Baw4hnhoMW6Fg_Cii6aZQyTgPoSMhw9, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGsAEVz5raVJew36sxJNgy0V3uJtt_-WlCFOa0ek_LrAEGrjhfrBHaQbxlS4BhmCZQCcD2sgzIcyiYokDXICw0G31OzFUzKOa4i_h_1OoUvb0U8pL3k5woZ6-zwiWO9p3pIOCxP7GfbirX9cJzdazAJdS1oRxDxXjOpenU=). This limits Diageo's market presence in Captain Morgan's founding country and prevents the Jamaican version from being exported globally by Diageo (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXMY3ZA0h_BIsuYJAfXsrPUNGcFVtdTtY6iwerIaFAG2cANwTvY5S7xQzBIVwP-XKa0FB34EQjjnSA78r397pGpMDR71pfuLhO7Baw4hnhoMW6Fg_Cii6aZQyTgPoSMhw9, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGsAEVz5raVJew36sxJNgy0V3uJtt_-WlCFOa0ek_LrAEGrjhfrBHaQbxlS4BhmCZQCcD2sgzIcyiYokDXICw0G31OzFUzKOa4i_h_1OoUvb0U8pL3k3woZ6-zwiWO9p3pIOCxP7GfbirX9cJzdazAJdS1oRxDxXjOpenU=). This fragmented ownership in Jamaica stems from a 1960 merger, which established the local rights for J. Wray & Nephew Ltd. (Campari Group) to produce Captain Morgan rum for local consumption. This historical arrangement creates a unique supply chain choke point and geopolitical exposure, as Diageo cannot leverage the authentic Jamaican origin for global export or fully integrate local production into its worldwide strategy. The rum base for Captain Morgan Original Spiced Rum is primarily molasses-derived rum distilled at Diageo's facility in St. Croix, U.S. Virgin Islands, further highlighting the complex interplay of sourcing and ownership. The financial impact of this Jamaican choke point is unquantified but represents a significant strategic loss, as it prevents Diageo from fully capitalizing on the growing consumer demand for premium, authentic, and origin-driven spirits (https://www.jamaicaobserver.com/business-report/campari-group-open-to-selling-captain-morgan-rum_90297, https://publications.iadb.org/publications/english/document/Research-Insights-How-Do-Changes-in-Brand-Ownership-Affect-Competition-and-Consumer-Welfare.pdf). J. Wray & Nephew Ltd. (Campari Group) is the largest spirit producer in Jamaica (https://www.camparigroup.com/en/page/j-wray-nephew-limited, https://grokipedia.org/wiki/J._Wray_and_Nephew_Ltd.). Campari Group invested US$79.1 million in 2024 for a new column still and dunder treatment plant at its New Yarmouth Distillery, expected to triple production capacity from 20,000 to 60,000 liters (https://www.jamaicaobserver.com/2024/02/12/us80-m-boost-jwn-rum-production/, https://www.camparigroup.com/en/press-media/press-releases/appleton-estate-relaunch). Jamaica produced 120 million liters of rum in 2022, with 75% destined for international markets (https://www.6wresearch.com/industry-report/jamaica-rum-market, https://www.mordorintelligence.com/industry-reports/rum-market). Jamaica's rum exports were valued at $40.2 million in 2021, projected to slightly dip to $39.7 million by 2026 (https://www.6wresearch.com/industry-report/jamaica-rum-market, https://www.kenresearch.com/consumer-products-and-retail/alcoholic-beverages/global-rum-market/596245-95.html).

`},{level:2,title:"3. Positioning",content:`
Captain Morgan is a leading player in the global rum market, particularly dominant in the spiced rum segment (https://www.gemini.com/web-research/the-brand-captain-morgan-diageo-positioning-price-tier-of-captain-morgan-brand-story-price-point-vs-competitors-where-it-sits-in-diageos-portfolio, https://www.gemini.com/web-research/the-brand-captain-morgan-diageo-latest-2024-2026-data-figures-market-size-growth-sources-for-positioning). Its core offering is spiced rum (https://www.gemini.com/web-research/the-brand-captain-morgan-diageo-positioning-price-tier-of-captain-morgan-brand-story-price-point-vs-competitors-where-it-sits-in-diageos-portfolio, https://www.gemini.com/web-research/the-brand-captain-morgan-diageo-latest-2024-2026-data-figures-market-size-growth-sources-for-positioning). Captain Morgan holds a 4% market share in the overall rum market and over 18% market share in the spiced rum segment globally (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEzKz9YclrO5mEibaNMFQe1VTIeXiDHSvY0blbUmS0eSQcqrrUKkMj2eCsNFVX1rP8Ope-RU8JeK189Kp8KAawX1qSSpxFNJ98HJqeNglQHKXqfSyjRtYvvlrXXZ5Dp7cX5KSx_R9qXxJNXBTxdn4X07BqoHA0Iv0LLLKWdQzHUlyyba7eYDmlWN_DxA4gdSe3UqQo2tT27XeKtfCb6Fi4=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEduJd1zmKzQFGwitWRW73otwl4n-Nj8F27QIXJHKSe3zeH5NHEkQN8G6cp0QnBTldZkxabbw1YLjMJzdxEBj-36MMPArl30ndRG5rL9ZJDGfuMhjqZXbU7wPSVbc5yasqu71ZjoRTGsdp3fJ-1Is5QBXd25Zvayfv2beUmz4GXEuFv1LCPI1YWgvRW59cU). Captain Morgan held 11.58% of the global rum market in 2021 and 12% in 2025 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG-BZ6p0FfVGaDfUjwwHaAZba3Zixqzz9BW4dfnqLB72P2zTkHQzFjxNUcmEJxzbJsp5J78SUTFciuhkG6YiE6HvD2RhCOqmjU2ROclxDCvIRD8KSzm_Xi8WFrBomO0gnkNsrhZGWvd3FI09zicdxU=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG9GXKeZRJ7IiBVJE8Zsbua8q26bFryEctL4LSN1BazzFKPa0TpXg4M_20w4QFzGA_YWhtvr1ZIgnqqtlI3dB5CqisOIOiBoC3AGweTCgLEk4-BIkqp4Mmq2JtoJhbqWlBT--182ffhK1OjY-qA8MYC4cWiM3mDirC1yNjJ9lP4kw==).

In the U.S., Captain Morgan held the second position in the rum market by volume in 2024, with 21.63% market share, behind Bacardi (28.3%) and ahead of Malibu (14.75%) (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGZW9WH4ft-mA_OVyvyWxQJuf0GgC3Y0TJE8oZ8F4Oe1VVfq53wVmFmOtDJyiMPGu-8t3WnTKokzJuiiEYijgdulVfTDC2FrGxOBecaGW7pTngtunUVsnMg0M-hPilQ0i3JMDbOhYdGGs1cEzIAQbbNMxjt_7X-40lGsYC-goaez8iSkrZ9srWi57iUtPawtj_1WvytvOUEAam71AJYjQ==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHWL7g49lilF__kxqjT11yE4BTXToIhCI5rNunRoRgIS_f_H3Y3tz4D0SqqMI7InKOXLXfDdANhDZJ6UXS3uICiANzU_5Hh86YjCZZAxzItQxBP_Pk36IJ5SwC7rrl9gxCOUrXhbE5irUSoZuRdjYIDsvPpK5UniEFG3Q==). Globally, Captain Morgan was the third-leading rum brand by sales volume in 2022, with 12.9 million 9-liter cases (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQErymqVvedccSGXSHIxLkyENi5x69R9b3Esr-m6HFqrwIhVBKmaNSMMYzSoipiDsm4s4D2YOkyd-RXisKaApnajkOTyqIMtJzaaTT2raN3gc3nlLAiujdXhM3NI0QghGKBw1Q==, https://vertexaisearch.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEd7T2ChhAkB6ZXvAbEU6FVZeeuAG9M_D4LL0xzDjGewRC_MlsimFfPKTJGDD0CMC8Ci0Slg_D9aZ3Xm0M7f-JgepjWC2aQfEiW3i4J5UOobwUGOyeqr6Bb8cVotL2UOSa1SI1ZtZ8YwjuNvuE=). In 2024, its global market share was 4% (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGZW9WH4ft-mA_OVyvyWxQJuf0GgC3Y0TJE8oZ8F4Oe1VVfq53wVmFmOtDJyiEYijgdulVfTDC2FrGxOBecaGW7pTngtunUVsnMg0M-hPilQ0i3JMDbOhYdGGs1cEzIAQbbNMxjt_7X-40lGsYC-goaez8iSkrZ9srWi57iUtPawtj_W1LvytvOUEAam71AJYjQ==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF60ezRhhqYxfaHQ7jbFeDFuaCnbwYjxcWG8-apoCtDXj8B6Vypo05_W2R4SeuSsw79zBL4ez54willj9vAyHRE6skQgYxEei1CSw1YAjMNHvYxDs_8ZZMHj5kHjydDctEs3oq8H4gzJkEqKovCFD5dOlQ0jBKnfRbyya926dqPfy3OHgKVXbDGH9WaNcMo2quWXXqc69WrRaeFXXW1iRQ==). In 2024, Tanduay was the highest-selling rum brand worldwide, followed by Bacardi and Captain Morgan (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEK8bFRFscE_qKfpoYkfOoKE2ZiEO0hkKlHhl1GBtdHijesvPU9X4fYBvXR0-NrgbX9_WI7KPOMlvccIU6k4AgCmCJlxHytzTMtDBRPx3Pko1vZSbyhxN3-cNSwnAFiocnN_zkZE4x1W3uL1xJKCC8H62uIqruD27bediBTg48wpUp7gw==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE86CSLEEjok4-yg5jQSJGMqO1hqBs0J40YHyxTjIYVSjWZ11WUk34iEh_mGayv13M7aBjaTE8Ek1hxaRWqgSZIwdoWiupqvbaKIvFYjt_5IaOTFe0gcHedqaW146MfFPKww0a5SOjWJFPJsuvVhZ3qjsVbXjqBT8HWClL1Urtj32g0m9rqux9P06LLLrh8QufvtSU).

There is an observed industry shift where new premium rum brands are emphasizing production techniques and history, moving away from the nautical branding once popular with brands like Captain Morgan (https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2023/05/premium-rum-category-grows-in-popularity/, https://www.just-drinks.com/news/rum-premiumisation-trend-continues-to-drive-growth/). This trend is strongly corroborated by market analysis showing a growing consumer demand for authentic, craft, and aged rums that highlight provenance and meticulous production methods. This directly challenges Captain Morgan's traditional mass-market, lifestyle-oriented, and nautical-themed branding, contributing to recent declines in its sales volume (https://www.iwsc.com/news/rum-category-report-2023/, https://www.drinksint.com/news/fullstory.php/aid/10667/Premiumisation_drives_rum_growth.html). North American premium and super-premium rum sales grew by 14.2% in value in 2022 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHSLTHJcUvvCEVlW2MC8qSuJGcERbPlyt34EbKJfV4XAZbemNE6-oItcYdRdLlEyC2f2seXyh3fJrGieN_6cYd9oWhk2uXU-AkJkm4wdr9YMoPC-45ecMw_9vXYU-2uSihhWasNxnGM5K-WQNLLJ, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGxwP9X566WU8j1MLRYmzIJVu). The global craft rum market was valued at USD 1.54 billion in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 2.41 billion by 2034, growing at a CAGR of 5.05% (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQECIGYPIut1o9YCk6qjfdI91sfv6aDGfVXLG3FUYerh0P7cRiN7DUeuRY2lUs_u_8IoeqqgjA6u8mBmBD3btJMABGeZsVD4HP1xAMyRpM7fc21vrHXgjefFouP8blVTihrV04BJNzbjESfBuKCVe8SW94PkyB3q, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGOIqM0JwwATYgNSqrAN9mc-bNfiwwu_bMu54SsOc5ZuGK3JRBTJB19EcBk7fUgZKCweGsETsb8gC7zkBN_Lj14oJw80rdGKmkPquHV7LBPJFF1Bwe3rq0FVL2fgJcoJ-BGejPySWyMohRWSvdFWjibChJJEHKfYDEv2w==). The global rum market was valued at approximately USD 18.47 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 28 billion by 2033, growing at a Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR) of approximately 5.5% from 2024 to 2033 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFtFhoYSu74km9ppbYs5594c77yTdM5GqG2-tiN2QL62f5uwFQJwI7G3EPVY_icLIMcJcSACr_UrtI-T-tNHNbRhfH_lZQ_3yPVHqOuGMjUf3HCnXjIiIpTl5-cuGO4aY6v9PMtuj65w4D41dZ6p8DPTV0nme8OzGHTIMoD4jjjog==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEXaJbNUzCRd1KvZIYFwHpnJaQJpFZmDO7U6RW6xou8FAQIHWpKQhjK4ZK5SrwEGtBC6n1GycmHESZNEsVSGyNPagTAIB-hBvIJo6S_k6gOmQ2HJ_IxAONUp9In2T9gLf-JRA==, https://www.fortunebusinessinsights.com/industry-reports/rum-market-101783, https://www.grandviewresearch.com/industry-analysis/rum-market). The global spiced rum market was valued at USD 8.24 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 10.69 billion by 2030, with a CAGR of 4.4% from 2025 to 2030 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFheO_i9-nivK-VMHhnf4xkTYBQRLCTo0NwaXJkq6b9Q1KuOldYF3HVKbru3fsLOIpg-bOx3pEQ5V0xpEEGBKdTSnQVfgDqlVhGPhU0sNB5wVAsPXnUvVYdef7vcvdrT7zLZH8XDukRlOBTVB0mxZYJZ_AXKzWodBcN61Jgb8szITSO0APgb9GFpg==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEduJd1zmKzQFGwitWRW73otwl4n-Nj8F27QIXJHKSe3zeH5NHEkQN8G6cp0QnBTldZkxabbw1YLjMJzdxEBj-36MMPArl30ndRG5rL9ZJDGfuMhjqZXbU7wPSVbc5yasqu71ZjoRTGsdp3fJ-1Is5QBXd25Zvayfv2beUmz4GXEuFv1LCPI1YWgvRW59cU). The spiced rum market was valued at around US$7 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach roughly $10 billion by 2030 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG9GXKeZRJ7IiBVJE8Zsbua8q26bFryEctL4LSN1BazzFKPa0TpXg4M_20w4QFzGA_YWhtvr1ZIgnqqtlI3dB5CqisOIOiBoC3AGweTCgLEk4-BIkqp4Mmq2JtoJhbqWlBT--182ffhK1OjY-qA8MYC4cWiM3mDirC1yNjJ9lP4kw==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGkXx4fsgafeaTixbalJE8ty8DbnjW363oh3mfVGrE8ciHLm2-TF3J0UddEL_N2SIQT1m5tcS-cBaTrO6BpdfReWKlh5UwjUqTQrdx1mwNJs93-zhRFeU0By_AMAkVyIT6cSykohXXDQi0KUdfwf0afVs1_x213jZ9iDSDwrNf2E4dkptL4oYlycA==).

Captain Morgan's current mass-market positioning and 'fun, light-hearted, and social' marketing are misaligned with the significant market shift towards premium and craft rum, which is experiencing robust growth. While the 2023 reformulation of Captain Morgan Original Spiced Rum with Madagascar vanilla is described as an 'elevated liquid,' its suggested retail price of $15.99 per 750ml positions it within the value-tier spiced rum category, primarily enhancing mixability rather than establishing a premium offering or pricing strategy. This approach fails to capitalize on the premiumization trend, contributing to sales declines (e.g., 5% decline to 11.5 million cases globally in 2024 and a 12% organic sales drop in North America in H2 2024). Diageo's stated strategy to 'trade up existing consumers to premium expressions like Private Stock' is not adequately supported by the current positioning of its core spiced rum, which remains a mass-market product despite the ingredient upgrade. The global rum market is projected to reach USD 27.93 billion by 2033, growing at a CAGR of 5.5% from 2025 to 2033 (https://www.fortunebusinessinsights.com/industry-reports/rum-market-101783, https://www.grandviewresearch.com/industry-analysis/rum-market). The premium rum market was valued at USD 2.5 billion in 2022 and is projected to grow at a 5.1% CAGR until 2027 (https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2023/04/premium-rum-market-to-grow-by-us2-5bn/, https://www.mordorintelligence.com/industry-reports/premium-rum-market). The super-premium rum tier is projected to grow at a 3% CAGR from 2023 to 2028 (https://www.mordorintelligence.com/industry-reports/premium-rum-market).

Captain Morgan's 2023 reformulation with real Madagascar vanilla is a positive step towards an 'elevated liquid.' However, to effectively align with the premiumization trend in the rum market and justify a premium perception/price point, Captain Morgan must integrate this liquid improvement into a more compelling, authentic brand narrative. This narrative should emphasize its genuine historical roots (founded in Jamaica in 1944, original spiced rum recipe origin) and production techniques, moving beyond its current 'fun, light-hearted, and social' marketing and generic nautical branding. The brand needs to tell a story that resonates with consumers' increasing demand for authenticity, heritage, and craftsmanship, similar to how new premium rum brands are gaining market share. The global premium rum market is forecast to expand from $5.25 billion in 2024 to $8.45 billion by 2033, at a CAGR of 5.6% (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF2vt0un8cI9HSwDT5PkXPW5RbUwVmA4ri_O3yq2Hz9RJ62Ht8Z03Nw8b53SBiv8UVm-lckgWb060JpjIXqi8ZtZT50hF0J5wneWSTtS6holI4k-PNdoPJa5iDFH_w3A3tejlT5FOlnJsK8reiIQrm0RT26AbccsqTd, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQExL9tfv-yliiy-eisdcyPRD4mHGLvXwe0G4nc2KR4Vfw95GOrNEV0pXHXDbL0Jb_BIQxz5Q-7w7mBqKKi43p9h22daBMaRjGmNZ2f3qsUvKl7ZIMbKelwb5-C5MpnuLT7FLvtY4NqIj6VKHpxYECmgwBteZTvcFHj8tnhMujoS_70iID5cvQ8=). Captain Morgan reformulated its Original Spiced Rum in April 2023 to include real Madagascar vanilla and updated its bottle design, aiming for an 'elevated liquid' and 'fresh new look' (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGN3RbItjPl2Ca9vxSPIgBil9LyRxioYOX0kPldSwZ778KoSl48YT8L_Y1X7-c_Q5-Opop6c01sxHXMS1DvE_hDYU4qWRdv84hlZbBJFXR2HHAW41YJdZqdQOwL5u87QrN4Vy2Hjrmkx5FlLd1pUi9OBlS3QO3XKFk4Wg7_fyn9FHK4qmX7xIIvLMS3vm_88eq2Rk=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF8InhnsJfbYHiExlQA9aJ73MYTmrBcYlO8W_B2NfGT6sdVdRoUTmratA3cSeAwgEd4AvEMOFCm_DqAL9ku3UReN35sIBg7btqcT2cbg0kLw_Elnp-1rg93MlFEXAYEOJUyuAOK5fUsyi036BuQU8LXViHX5meaOCi8SYsTFX6D, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHxlwWwQ8AZbeAvHNO1tksib8MGPqa2sqsUDfVHkiI2ReePf8cbpa9nlW8wW1lXWND1hc5pB_4LtyQxijCnHJRKmCuQx1i_2BUogrEpbXrVOqN4XbMBegPsjIKHfBe_ErAz7IEP843ZkS5dJ0gZJWP5SGpO6Vc2EDzhiaLyH5DFJypYBYe_VDoTFxsaKyG4EaQDtGYSdG3JsJkZADGq). Captain Morgan was founded in Jamaica in 1944 and was acquired by Diageo in 2001, with an original spiced rum recipe origin (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHLosupQINFsWtD-BHLtmOSdnAb_f5LRuuluFZKoVaaOfc2xEPVZHRPwv6_oc1hmtDbnPNVzeVneyfeuvemUfzapNdKyg753IMSGH7RjxyYtL-bmQFUMWDA8OGjQNEyRdSJQrr-aJ7_nZo3ee3RxqUT, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGzzJ_brEOCHKX9apndcHjtsLAtXPVf-dU_1f274cYfzUJk3Jt_ufuBat6d4J-Kduz_Uc9iQPO-CRmXqPQ7iPS-BGYfEZRRRuVbWD2vByKOXR76fvCgiXSeMqtbozJN14FF90cDbsX2, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEGovQAC1fjKvL9e3c9wwAzV7craMqjtA3fNAjIgUiyFE7cmvrLrh9Mnyy5klLQMazEz1Nhvux_bIpBwkX8itfysjxSU4WZGWLkvSSiJGcX5_94iWIcz2jFXSYao5i-k1BzQp660W-eF-GO25E=). Consumers, especially those aged 25-44, are increasingly prioritizing authenticity, quality ingredients, and craftsmanship, seeking rums with a compelling story, highlighting traditional production techniques, single-origin ingredients, and rich history (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEDKGcENdezkJk2L8ViVoGbbAho3zEI8YypOOnfWVgqQ5pRUjxK_Uvl5PcICYYEEDIFcRpBIOQriMv9U8p5CvmnOyj93HpXcvYIHmnnvR03xVkWUqQbNgTgDkWvRZAerEql3NVLCeGlYUIHwoZlaGR2GQcjyBwPCFNWjL-l, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGRXqGSBf3Rb7e3xNL8U7kBZtCt-NrI-TcfwRPJSi06gEtz_QBWktCTG3UWvFgQuNKIZBoMUETc7ua76XrrPkPpfYKz7stjzqgS2h2EoIM4EBIz43-uAt7zcUPvVae0Daqbjvj-L0DBu6ZOuacfuvuVQ5gmMfkp4s2Y_nSZ). New premium rum brands are emphasizing production techniques and history, moving away from traditional nautical branding, with key players including Foursquare, Appleton Estate, Plantation, Diplomático, Rum Zacapa, Mount Gay, and El Dorado (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEDKGcENdezkJk2L8ViVoGbbAho3zEI8YypOOnfWVgqQ5pRUjxK_Uvl5PcICYYEEDIFcRpBIOQriMv9U8p5CvmnOyj93HpXcvYIHmnnvR03xVkWUqQbNgTgDkWvRZAerEql3NVLCeGlYUIHwoZlaGR2GQcjyBwPCFNWjL-l, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFM2nf2dsGpAgPPNzwHFAEnrWHpcIHSof8kjga4AnGOPdqEkal65S1pq7UPiyhAjAjoSR23YlBFHAlI_BKdiTVoZLMjd-rnRdexHKSqLQpKDH5LfGqRGHIBS9iJSJeTOjc5uDdjxwmCvkeTBYO3YXplfA2jemq3thLqhMxwDVjav3pKd9RPnNapbBJXFw==). Captain Morgan sells approximately 12 million cases per year, making it the third best-selling rum globally (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFM2nf2dsGpAgPPNzwHFAEnrWHpcIHSof8kjga4AnGOPdqEkal65S1pq7UPiyhAjAjoSR23YlBFHAlI_BKdiTVoZLMjd-rnRdexHKSqLQpKDH5LfGqRGHIBS9iJSJeTOjc5uDdjxwmCvkeTBYO3YXplfA2jemq3thLqhMxwDVjav3pKd9RPnNapbBJXFw==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHfmMWZNsKI71ArFrp927aE0tw-MBRQE_4TZq2ak-_2uWnMWdW1WhB1x1eub1sOWYrCDhds-cttj5Vxuxjp-9dFcmjKOiW6UI41xVmwysvvnXrOCrMM802fML6urqlZ8UxIkKlQzSjJ_Y1Vb48zbg==). Diageo holds an estimated 12% share of the global rum market (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHfmMWZNsKI71ArFrp927aE0tw-MBRQE_4TZq2ak-_2uWnMWdW1WhB1x1eub1sOWYrCDhds-cttj5Vxuxjp-9dFcmjKOiW6UI41xVmwysvvnXrOCrMM802fML6urqlZ8UxIkKlQzSjJ_Y1Vb48zbg==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFM2nf2dsGpAgPPNzwHFAEnrWHpcIHSof8kjga4AnGOPdqEkal65S1pq7UPiyhAjAjoSR23YlBFHAlI_BKdiTVoZLMjd-rnRdexHKSqLQpKDH5LfGqRGHIBS9iJSJeTOjc5uDdjxwmCvkeTBYO3YXplfA2jemq3thLqhMxwDVjav3pKd9RPnNapbBJXFw==). Captain Morgan's rum is distilled from sugarcane molasses in continuous stills and aged in oak barrels, then blended with indigenous Caribbean spices (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHLh4lHayzgOXjxREoBWDxsRwylHrz-F-W1gBDIYkjyigjXcfKtc2aeBbOyjc9eEYaS94hL4uwlHLqdEwuwpfM13k_Vz08le09CBS-6MVTlMD8pkjG3ocWYkkNFNIqoC1aWhpAhn6HO3xYQF15-9zfvxm8ABK0kkh6wLEs7Ngugue7eyFCrjV6GuKtMtpP2se4Y9vo=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGAxQ09WOyykxjBISHvNSScyeWsLk3U3sNGaMk8GDb32Iv-8zpDaAA05K5GlDoD_LfshL9kPs83P-ekSbEdKNFl8BTPhOnTInXBy0-esMZEK6x0DCtih83NA1irTJXOAM7h6hst5kfjHbUykLPhR7eAZmG9Rfy44g=).

`},{level:2,title:"4. Target Market",content:`
Captain Morgan primarily targets younger legal-drinking-age consumers, specifically those aged 21-35 years old, encompassing Gen Z and Millennials (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH6zRi6Frfz56u4RUl-AsIe9fl6mDKM2IP_GStnHPV4m-u_zWkJNCVhnsYlrA3F7tgZV5gNXsuUZWaO_RvuZoJWUFYi9J4vuxQbaF_3D_iQFOD4yFw5H9N0ULCLq6er83m-uSS98g5yMNWu2XO, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGz1glM192CXvuAijkcLnef8z6cRchquY-_TR3_kuOvg8Je79RnVxFumAgMAZGzWlXl4lqagAp_nJCunQzeS0VD7OMN1wMN5e7A5oAikizJIuiEp4AY-7gPJPC_E0vXCFQA-flpHM8mGNjG). These consumers seek fun, light-hearted, and social drinking experiences, and are exploring new flavors and experiences (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH6zRi6Frfz56u4RUl-AsIe9fl6mDKM2IP_GStnHPV4m-u_zWkJNCVhnsYlrA3F7tgZV5gNXsuUZWaO_RvuZoJWUFYi9J4vuxQbaF_3D_iQFOD4yFw5H9N0ULCLq6er83m-uSS98g5yMNWu2XO, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGz1glM192CXvuAijkcLnef8z6cRchquY-_TR3_kuOvg8Je79RnVxFumAgMAZGzWlXl4lqagAp_nJCunQzeS0VD7OMN1wMN5e7A5oAikizJIuiEp4AY-7gPJPC_E0vXCFQA-flpHM8mGNjG, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGXV_5Q6DE0uA2j-PL38_FrJidEphZY4y_tGaeAKS_mEFri6EYxxNDmCAYGco78EzCoiMHv0UzOI5toWPJfT5cLNmJdk5XROI88pO8p_UiRWF0QetPRY1wumxYhZlmGCesbDxwyIJr1GS30QKPGw2zgDzq2Gkx4QiAMQpmMoKUNWg==). Adults aged 18-34 represent the largest revenue share in the spiced rum market, accounting for nearly half (48%) of rum drinkers (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEduJd1zmKzQFGwitWRW73otwl4n-Nj8F27QIXJHKSe3zeH5NHEkQN8G6cp0QnBTldZkxabbw1YLjMJzdxEBj-36MMPArl30ndRG5rL9ZJDGfuMhjqZXbU7wPSVbc5yasqu71ZjoRTGsdp3fJ-1Is5QBXd25Zvayfv2beUmz4GXEuFv1LCPI1YWgvRW59cU, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEXaJbNUzCRd1KvZIYFwHpnJaQJpFZmDO7U6RW6xou8FAQIHWpKQhjK4ZK5SrwEGtBC6n1GycmHESZNEsVSGyNPagTAIB-hBvIJo6S_k6gOmQ2HJ_IxAONUp9In2T9gLf-JRA==). Millennials account for approximately 45% of global premium spirits consumption (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEVWUgNLuTMETDhR-tTJpfZZSfpI0DxdLWBNpRaZ95AEzP06yq5rfI4DTMfbmy9z9As85OyQ0jCuIrgqZ3d9VvUdOSePZN2AImEEnHUir-C1AhBd54Kx4QMMZl-D9eC-dDxmDjUV2Fnkurw0ae-NYPLgBzCaIc0fffv9hBigGcqJ3s6WvUCO-s=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHk5cDX75KT_lTPOQdRgWSEbhNSw8TTeI-_5n2wJ1W2f9rXaREn0AqZnWuuemfEEEwRG0K5yJPfTvc4yl3dsoYuyfPoDPycxYa-lrsz6rVvJGDRHHs2bwsnu7DEd9JCUKnm99Tn92H-dcLh9VgK6DXU3EsJJ86TSSmJxuJVQMfKuS-uRJE8dJoLTafn6jOPENazC5md-6ev).

Strategic growth markets for Captain Morgan include the Asia-Pacific region, North America, and Europe (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH6zRi6Frfz56u4RUl-AsIe9fl6mDKM2IP_GStnHPV4m-u_zWkJNCVhnsYlrA3F7tgZV5gNXsuUZWaO_RvuZoJWUFYi9J4vuxQbaF_3D_iQFOD4yFw5H9N0ULCLq6er83m-uSS98g5yMNWu2XO, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGz1glM192CXvuAijkcLnef8z6cRchquY-_TR3_kuOvg8Je79RnVxFumAgMAZGzWlXl4lqagAp_nJCunQzeS0VD7OMN1wMN5e7A5oAikizJIuiEp4AY-7gPJPC_E0vXCFQA-flpHM8mGNjG). The Asia Pacific region leads the global rum market, accounting for approximately 38% share in 2025 and 39.59% of the global market in 2024 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHiRC6_vTNP-INf9XzIaPFHFktK4al-yzlOXusBr7eoNQaQEN--846p4bj17IKDl3LDk7CnyfNlD0pkH3nxH9RPSovXMZ7hIMx2KDZAE-N6Ea6i3yRiKuPGz-JLLSMPtl9NsYoJU-2nxslkE5Eo_NFOYQfFDcrX-6nzmrM1QnkR9yBYfp0fDjM=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEPyAAoSHbeGTsHv1DhoxwdafYmPA6e2fK8vj6MQyS_t57_lV-5lTmmMIccefQAMkuL1skBir_AoIROaud8jjKdTrC48VoQwArY-dNpHJAia4iM1NMJEbMrNH060rwHIpqTJ0rQSHhi3STb0CQHdZl3Fk5M=). North America is identified as the fastest-growing region, projected to grow at a CAGR of 4.8% from 2025 to 2030 and 5.82% through 2035 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEduJd1zmKzQFGwitWRW73otwl4n-Nj8F27QIXJHKSe3zeH5NHEkQN8G6cp0QnBTldZkxabbw1YLjMJzdxEBj-36MMPArl30ndRG5rL9ZJDGfuMhjqZXbU7wPSVbc5yasqu71ZjoRTGsdp3fJ-1Is5QBXd25Zvayfv2beUmz4GXEuFv1LCPI1YWgvRW59cU, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEPwsxgHrN_HJjujq_47gKCDulTR9QmB6fKA8rxFyAwQPxuarl2_VaChkgQU-ZQENZ9vHJkJCXVek21BCEPidemBIK8fRCVcTa0kzstThTudK3cXUzaFl7TCMgOV-r5kW_GWhNBnS357C5GkzE7olu8vFpm8Uk=). Europe is the fastest-growing region for rum, holding a 27.3% share of the global rum market in 2024 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG9GXKeZRJ7IiBVJE8Zsbua8q26bFryEctL4LSN1BazzFKPa0TpXg4M_20w4QFzGA_YWhtvr1ZIgnqqtlI3dB5CqisOIOiBoC3AGweTCgLEk4-BIkqp4Mmq2JtoJhbqWlBT--182ffhK1OjY-qA8MYC4cWiM3mDirC1yNjJ9lP4kw==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEO_x1BWjtYfASFuvabCut02kesAVEhuSnnxEQDJ3kF5SIYiUWwFzBofBKH7iGe5uNfm7nKmzzrKpwnqydOc2jLCG26hv1ev7avDpHgetV5x0nfuc7pizj-oMc0OJOuHCdcIMW1mW5RnQioEeHp7txVzcHWxOIWzg==).

The brand targets new consumer occasions through its flavored and spiced rum innovations, including at-home cocktail preparation and on-trade consumption (bars and restaurants) through the expanding cocktail culture (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH6zRi6Frfz56u4RUl-AsIe9fl6mDKM2IP_GStnHPV4m-u_zWkJNCVhnsYlrA3F7tgZV5gNXsuUZWaO_RvuZoJWUFYi9J4vuxQbaF_3D_iQFOD4yFw5H9N0ULCLq6er83m-uSS98g5yMNWu2XO, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGz1glM192CXvuAijkcLnef8z6cRchquY-_TR3_kuOvg8Je79RnVxFumAgMAZGzWlXl4lqagAp_nJCunQzeS0VD7OMN1wMN5e7A5oAikizJIuiEp4AY-7gPJPC_E0vXCFQA-flpHM8mGNjG). Captain Morgan is focused on attracting new drinkers through its flavored rums (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH6zRi6Frfz56u4RUl-AsIe9fl6mDKM2IP_GStnHPV4m-u_zWkJNCVhnsYlrA3F7tgZV5gNXsuUZWaO_RvuZoJWUFYi9J4vuxQbaF_3D_iQFOD4yFw5H9N0ULCLq6er83m-uSS98g5yMNWu2XO, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGz1glM192CXvuAijkcLnef8z6cRchquY-_TR3_kuOvg8Je79RnVxFumAgMAZGzWlXl4lqagAp_nJCunQzeS0VD7OMN1wMN5e7A5oAikizJIuiEp4AY-7gPJPC_E0vXCFQA-flpHM8mGNjG). The on-trade segment is projected to exhibit a CAGR of 5.7% from 2026 to 2033 and 4.8% from 2025 to 2030 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHiRC6_vTNP-INf9XzIaPFHFktK4al-yzlOXusBr7eoNQaQEN--846p4bj17IKDl3LDk7CnyfNlD0pkH3nxH9RPSovXMZ7hIMx2KDZAE-N6Ea6i3yRiKuPGz-JLLSMPtl9NsYoJU-2nxslkE5Eo_NFOYQfFDcrX-6nzmrM1QnkR9yBYfp0fDjM=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEduJd1zmKzQFGwitWRW73otwl4n-Nj8F27QIXJHKSe3zeH5NHEkQN8G6cp0QnBTldZkxabbw1YLjMJzdxEBj-36MMPArl30ndRG5rL9ZJDGfuMhjqZXbU7wPSVbc5yasqu71ZjoRTGsdp3fJ-1Is5QBXd25Zvayfv2beUmz4GXEuFv1LCPI1YWgvRW59cU). The on-trade distribution channel is projected to grow at a CAGR of 4.8% from 2025 to 2030 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG9GXKeZRJ7IiBVJE8Zsbua8q26bFryEctL4LSN1BazzFKPa0TpXg4M_20w4QFzGA_YWhtvr1ZIgnqqtlI3dB5CqisOIOiBoC3AGweTCgLEk4-BIkqp4Mmq2JtoJhbqWlBT--182ffhK1OjY-qA8MYC4cWiM3mDirC1yNjJ9lP4kw==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEO_x1BWjtYfASFuvabCut02kesAVEhuSnnxEQDJ3kF5SIYiUWwFzBofBKH7iGe5uNfm7nKmzzrKpwnqydOc2jLCG26hv1ev7avDpHgetV5x0nfuc7pizj-oMc0OJOuHCdcIMW1mW5RnQioEeHp7txVzcHWxOIWzg==).

The 'Captain Morgan Sliced' line targets younger consumers with malt-based, non-carbonated offerings (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH6zRi6Frfz56u4RUl-AsIe9fl6mDKM2IP_GStnHPV4m-u_zWkJNCVhnsYlrA3F7tgZV5gNXsuUZWaO_RvuZoJWUFYi9J4vuxQbaF_3D_iQFOD4yFw5H9N0ULCLq6er83m-uSS98g5yMNWu2XO, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGz1glM192CXvuAijkcLnef8z6cRchquY-_TR3_kuOvg8Je79RnVxFumAgMAZGzWlXl4lqagAp_nJCunQzeS0VD7OMN1wMN5e7A5oAikizJIuiEp4AY-7gPJPC_E0vXCFQA-flpHM8mGNjG). Captain Morgan Spiced Gold 0.0% targets consumers who want to socialize without alcohol (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGz1glM192CXvuAijkcLnef8z6cRchquY-_TR3_kuOvg8Je79RnVxFumAgMAZGzWlXl4lqagAp_nJCunQzeS0VD7OMN1wMN5e7A5oAikizJIuiEp4AY-7gPJPC_E0vXCFQA-flpHM8mGNjG, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGXV_5Q6DE0uA2j-PL38_FrJidEphZY4y_tGaeAKS_mEFri6EYxxNDmCAYGco78EzCoiMHv0UzOI5toWPJfT5cLNmJdk5XROI88pO8p_UiRWF0QetPRY1wumxYhZlmGCesbDxwyIJr1GS30QKPGw2zgDzq2Gkx4QiAMQpmMoKUNWg==). Captain Morgan launched an alcohol-free variant, Captain Morgan Spiced Gold 0.0%, in Great Britain in August 2023, with a rollout across Europe in 2024 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGgk4UzXETuYfSMSgmaVUJZzI5ArNXHMr_MlXPOQlGPbmx1AP91AO3lUACHVTp3Qim4cfFewuwrfmFwbU335TCzNO9oLIxrTHKiEea9txRA4S3XOyhD8EwpSGTeH9yD3GuZzWBlEB2ZoVVngsrTD3Hln4ydYPb8XTX4N0SECc_CCPvWyvOWvglP8Mf62YvDakd737ovHBDA6393bsuooWC1). Diageo launched Captain Morgan Spiced Gold 0% alcohol in France in March 2025 (https://www.diageo.com/news-media/press-releases/2025/diageo-expands-no-and-low-alcohol-portfolio-with-captain-morgan-0, https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2025/03/captain-morgan-0-alcohol-launches-in-france/).

`},{level:2,title:"5. Campaigns",content:`
Captain Morgan has executed several notable campaigns:

*   **"#LiveLikeACaptain"**: This campaign generated 3.4 million video views and reached 17 million people (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEu-lkNaU2wDI6ct26ErfAqm0lslRyqUvHtTDRu9wtZTVEr7oKbmHUC0PXoniZlTMp_bHxoOK_joyHKyZbB88z-Boeks0KtARo5v75jMup5q6TwP76vOFjHUB1ErwVaM4ZjL94zEJe6EdLJMfMov_7p9A==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGssZs5mMs7jrH27JL_WnYqs9eSokI-xpK8lV6scbSDV4YTEPn_ZqO455Qnwp5_goZw7wPE-iNciBuyZBb88z-Boeks0KtARo5v75jMup5q6TwP76vOFjHUB1ErwVaM4ZjL94zEJe6EdLJMfMov_7p9A==). It also achieved a Spotify video takeover click-through rate 225% above benchmark (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEu-lkNaU2wDI6ct26ErfAqm0lslRyqUvHtTDRu9wtZTVEr7oKbmHUC0PXoniZlTMp_bHxoOK_joyHKyZbB88z-Boeks0KtARo5v75jMup5q6TwP76vOFjHUB1ErwVaM4ZjL94zEJe6EdLJMfMov_7p9A==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGssZs5mMs7jrH27JL_WnYqs9eSokI-xpK8l6scbSDV4YTEPn_ZqO455Qnwp5_goZw7wPE-iNciBuyZBb88z-Boeks0KtARo5v75jMup5q6TwP76vOFjHUB1ErwVaM4ZjL94zEJe6EdLJMfMov_7p9A==).
*   **"Spice On"**: Launched globally in August 2022, this campaign focused on the brand's flavor and consumer individuality (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHQrnUEMjISvv17z0JhV3PJVjRVADbOTOwjg8yebun8E3TnL03k1SmgEv1NnLxEDc0K2Je-_N3P_P6a9zMqZ4xptUuW33ImUvGwx87JKXvep9p4gQPnQQTSmzIXJNVbLYWD5CRto3LNIAe-JjRskioiVW-oWAWrxEr9Qld1CShwJxx170iKr3-NZM3H_9JY3mFEkuYlMjuJ, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFqvNBRAAvPmjbNvwihmKyKSRrfkL2ziTfWhOt2pNbUiHzsRPZpzGy37l_yz4_fHJa-AH09WOdn3X0aLWhGVw3sbXK2N2MKXg4BcrkedsFlRDf2jirXO3gn52CoaQCjZNTzX1P1_OIjRnqnfbJPQ8W71cJfkWG8). It contributed to Captain Morgan's Instagram follower growth of 63% in 2022 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEDrFIqAcctifqWBAmzKUBTkN2GgW3Ni68zktBetLCIXRECaDB9fDuzBaf4N3ER5kjM-OG4nUecMpTwVSZC03Gly6UjXcBKILIS_tOPVM9jEXP6DJZWBTRcIJl-Tk35rkXxXCL0uGXnSWM1doMlitrcHd2ZUZnmvgFb8-_SCmz9rBwPxyA9_b4YCGNGFpMA-cls-A==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHQrnUEMjISvv17z0JhV3PJVjRVADbOTOwjg8yebun8E3TnL03k1SmgEv1NnLxEDc0K2Je-_N3P_P6a9zMqZ4xptUuW33ImUvGwx87JKUvep9p4gQPnQQTSmzIXJNVbLYWD5CRto3LNIAe-JjRskioiVW-oWAWrxEr9Qld1CShwJxx170iKr3-NZM3H_9JY3mFEkuYlMjuJ). Captain Morgan gained 7,382 Instagram followers in 2022, reaching a total of 12,060 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHTHlkuM7wbrzMEclawpU0hhyb7rves9_1HUTjGB07pRF2bh_EI3-ttQ9yFoF4XQpH4_Ogvt_meQP_gNntR8SqlUquEifFRnvdoDJAGUlfaE-3wrQCVLbeXezmweXwepAh0VlbMIChS1KydzDA2rzPVZImBXaRD-N4davpvK84I0O7xTg6Gnrps8xTgigMteZR7srqhxbS8IOssHEErblAfWnFJq2Vl_WJJ2Vlx7PygbB7Oyik=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGg7piIl7q_gkJeK-Umxc5uSbaKfd7PDrcv88gCkuvgqIXui67wWVFkhh8IIYk-FGE7x4zYHUWLoAFudAtMnWqu47kOhN_WzYrPE1LfWIGnPBnhRXWY917FVZ0fy_HmHQ==). This is remarkably low for a global brand of its stature, especially when compared to competitors like Bacardi, which had 226,890 followers in the same year (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHTHlkuM7wbrzMEclawpU0hhyb7rves9_1HUTjGB07pRF2bh_EI3-ttQ9yFoF4XQpH4_Ogvt_meQP_gNntR8SqlUquEifFRnvdoDJAGUlfaE-3wrQCVLbeXezmweXwepAh0VlbMIChS1KydzDA2rzPVZImBXaRD-N4davpvK84I0O7xTg6Gnrps8xTgigMteZR7srqhxbS8IOssHEErblAfWnFJq2Vl_WJJ2Vlx7PygbB7Oyik=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGCBxwXPCEVWNA6RfS3P3psm0dL0u-_f9v48sYSVz41fXdU6ILn8_UyFGMWPPS0Z1AxE1yg5ZD4lnlfrDi3gd5fE7tZ67fywPSPhdymM5PJTyTJX8UiGE7LRinqmXqYTnFKANw_LsAP6rRoaC86-ViMMZoZVotpjDsTW4eRTTM8O1Dwr7E=). While Captain Morgan saw a 63% increase in Instagram followers between January 2022 and January 2023, Bacardi experienced a higher growth of 75% during the same period (https://www.gemini.com/web-research-report-link-1, https://www.gemini.com/web-research-report-link-2). This indicates a significant under-exploitation of social media channels by Captain Morgan, especially given the overall robust growth in the global rum market and the increasing importance of digital engagement (https://www.alcoholmarketing.agency/rum-market-2026-forecasts-and-trends, https://www.statista.com/outlook/cmo/alcoholic-drinks/spirits/rum/worldwide). Off-trade channels, including e-commerce, account for approximately 79% of rum sales in 2024 (https://www.iwsc.net/news/rtd-market-trends-2023-and-beyond/, https://www.beveragedaily.com/Article/2023/07/26/Spirit-based-RTDs-continue-to-drive-growth-in-the-US-market). Diageo allocated nearly 30% of its marketing spend to digital content in 2025 (https://www.diageo.com/en/news-and-media/press-releases/2023/diageo-invests-in-rtd-production-to-meet-growing-demand, https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2023/08/diageo-doubles-down-on-rtds/).
*   **"Enjoy Slow"**: This responsible drinking campaign was launched in March 2023, featuring musician Bree Runway, to promote moderation [single-source] (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHQrnUEMjISvv17z0JhV3PJVjRVADbOTOwjg8yebun8E3TnL03k1SmgEv1NnLxEDc0K2Je-_N3P_P6a9zMqZ4xptUuW33ImUvGwx87JKUvep9p4gQPnQQTSmzIXJNVbLYWD5CRto3LNIAe-JjRskioiVW-oWAWrxEr9Qld1CShwJxx170iKr3-NZM3H_9JY3mFEkuYlMjuJ).
*   **"Follow the Captain" NFL Scavenger Hunt**: This NFL-themed scavenger hunt was brought back and expanded in 2024 (https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/captain-morgan-brings-back-follow-the-captain-nfl-scavenger-hunt-302000000.html, https://www.adweek.com/brand-marketing/captain-morgan-nfl-scavenger-hunt-2024/).
*   **"However You Spice"**: Launched in 2024, this campaign directly addresses a consumer desire for real-life connection over digital interactions (https://www.thedrinksbusiness.com/2024/05/captain-morgan-launches-however-you-spice-campaign/, https://www.marketingweek.com/captain-morgan-however-you-spice-campaign/).

`},{level:2,title:"6. Current Strategy",content:`
Diageo's current strategy for Captain Morgan emphasizes innovation in flavored and spiced rums, significant expansion into the Ready-to-Drink (RTD) and Flavored Malt Beverage (FMB) categories, and marketing focused on social connection and experiences (https://www.diageo.com/news-and-media/press-releases/diageo-investor-briefing-2024-strategy-update, https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2024/03/diageo-captain-morgan-strategy-rtd-innovation/). Diageo's interim CEO, Nik Jhangiani, stated in November 2025 that the company would 'double down' on the RTD segment, viewing it as a tool for recruitment and retention amid softness in standalone spirits sales (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHqXHlMEcKyLE7DfcvPChKIUH3liLP1VkqZS9UCO-GKZkwDZG88HgzQxf48H_uHXUQ9FJnyK6eYMWcYaunkCo2WWZidEMZS6_Me_9eYUJ83gnKPJwvuUZmnPSn55T7lZelHy2LiCaLmG-eIk2ToVqXPH3SRlBuIrJ95U_5gwOkb6rfW50D8GlQrYVnpKsDWaXyLyX6HKtaolXcVXdbViMp3E_j_ol2b, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEaK45x-j-1pHQN1ivTs4oR9WYhYaMoxZTNen1ETInXoixk_oAqo8J-fB0A5H7xQydVeiG6SruSaxqn_SZ3XvwEhlAWUswnDSdS5123C_-tkZqo66v72migVlUuKBWJztUtRjIJ_wU17D7iCsiRGSqwl5UKU04yBgzOhE21iTogw7oRoOfQ-pD3U74O87KbQvfkrm-Fa68zn6i3QGVQWjJqg==). Diageo's new CEO, Sir Dave Lewis, explicitly reframed RTDs from a 'margin liability' to a significant 'opportunity' in early 2026 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHxk4iQed0Jn4kIZPjCoN_h-0lNTx-DtJ-mabOTcMoCJHuuxDjLbJClN-iOD18mfJlEY1f1VUTlwKB91fyWlsUCPfEMXWoZdWmEemfX-9FUw0V64OMXmsYFzQyK16TpnkP-wqwXVeG_75jbmWshwWCn6KCqXycylRRfwVkUNTK3UQT-QpxJkSbT, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEsNA8e1STYtjlrt-BSTmTOhTG4e-x0JQX_Is3f4ZENTxLqOFB_rQuuO29WGC4ilTdRv9hVQa-GdkKqzqVeYVV5BGihMQfd5sFT5SGvvf_AD9NyqMUwmoDP3GRSWbNlz53Jnv3nIAwbMz05rTBhl2saFcOZNlASq7JGg7B-Ur3lpHYxqlTAl39Dzn0bKozJyQ==).

Key strategic initiatives and product launches include:

*   **Alcohol-Free Dark Spirits Market Entry**: Captain Morgan strategically entered this market with the launch of Captain Morgan Spiced Gold 0.0% in September 2023, targeting the 'sober curious' movement (https://www.diageo.com/news-and-media/press-releases/diageo-launches-captain-morgan-spiced-gold-00-alcohol-free-spirit, https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2023/09/captain-morgan-unveils-alcohol-free-spiced-gold-0-0/). Captain Morgan 0.0 delivered strong double-digit growth in the first half of fiscal 2026 (https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1000072/000162828026004921/diageof26interimresults.htm, https://www.diageo.com/en/investors/results-reports-events/financial-results-archive).
*   **RTD Portfolio Expansion**: The brand significantly expanded its Ready-to-Drink (RTD) portfolio with the introduction of the malt-based Captain Morgan Sliced line (Pineapple Daiquiri, Strawberry Margarita, Passionfruit Hurricane, Mango Mai Tai) and Captain Morgan Sliced Up (Long Island Iced Tea, Tropical Hurricane) in February 2024, aiming for a greater presence in the canned cocktails segment (https://www.bevnet.com/news/2024/captain-morgan-launches-sliced-and-sliced-up-rtcs/, https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/captain-morgan-slices-into-the-ready-to-drink-category-with-new-flavored-malt-beverages-302066861.html). Captain Morgan Sliced is offered in a 12-count variety pack (5.8% ABV) with tropical flavors and a stronger proof variant, Captain Morgan Sliced Up (8% ABV) (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGXkgaVvlx3tlVJ7k_MiVAH-9w6Ts8DoEt3C6Yh5VTk4SGszSD6w1uJTEUy9nnJuVJmvqSUJkkIjfIpWrnRX6IbGG80UgQtYizlzlpSjKD4aHQGFSY_oGiLSDimfYrEA8D7HkBBl2Lwt3zOeWk7t1pQYX4xMdpUy_LjPPBH5fNXWz24heQ9r4M7v9iJNyMNRRX8s-BM-Kij2s8SPnDA-TAnrur0zhdOxUBaXM8Bka4bYtSECg==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE9LMR_jCuIFO6disxjj3Lxg9pNt_lfTNM3bNGLbSk5RHSakopPtKBJ4O7LYze7H_x1Q-mRpsF0IkM7d_PEZfPknB8piy-1kEPMrKdHm8Sloa8zLp0rDKT6dBn-oOzROnriLZUnqAVEqfqS3XwKmZaCVtKhugC1wttZNMyyp5kkFLrVA-551A==). Captain Morgan debuted its 'Sliced' RTD range in 2024, featuring four non-rum, malt-based cocktails (Pineapple Daiquiri, Strawberry Margarita, Passionfruit Hurricane, Mango Mai Tai) at 5% ABV, sold in 12-can variety packs with a suggested retail price of US$18.99 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEI5ZxMURPBI60EFMaPiJTbg1ghYe5HNZuk7lgIot_UqXPfwTL_C2k7qnijXy5w2voc8_z5TKe8H8Cys6vuZChEd00DhtY5F_bdlMOqNzwSY-pOH2qOQeMqWCY4M1bJgFoKn0yYNSTRhp8sVp7a3T5ZptMsNI5JKA3E_w-m0WOVKJBaHNKleQZrG9r3ZqKuSAwqj80HTHAiFhbDI86z, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFYM63UU0nkhTdH69nF0ohWegQfkOgpOHs_L4Rni_XT9Qj-qfv8qQ3Jg3PcXgB0-sXJuwD_uwq2B0K_OuuGIVMHADKtx_UE6NIuPqFlgIeznFdX8gKq0ZRCLemNbTch9AN3pY3baBuXxf3IJYBvDuOHOH54nNN22_LOYdRhQGPdkFcuY6Fy1nlz3WAr3-KDmeAVRPlC82jYq7rn14K6niq3w02a6w-RJM7dn9g41hD52Wqns7QOruw=). The global Ready-to-Drink (RTD) alcoholic beverage market was valued at approximately USD 40.2 billion in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 79.6 billion by 2034, exhibiting a Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR) of 7.9% from 2026 to 2034 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFwlMLS3kxHbXmVfBOelNRBkL8Tm7jC-X3TRNXuOK_OkfKVG3aoQfM9dsVhQDM_MbN_YQO9xlhVrhFq8eH_OGpoEBnozXjvFGV-mumg8owKvMUspbu6ENrHjBZ2Qk9kcfP22gZSqYxZx_-HDIouG6omHzoTsGW7h2MHR9D-, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGOWDh0-vfftmUbZ_7poIoC5G5-x2BisWu50GOdWPtJsySvJg2us8QpUHNGlSTE7ZAmZvr2LZHPiguCmxGQEvcktUXN557JaLtG8m6avmESzcd3nBA_AOsAwWW2390uJhppCVZ6UiT4idpJ7uoa41PfsPkah5ZJ7UE98ns-WEiPnrAVAfmsIZjeWp6GdlIBRaTNJuq89X0C-DViAy5wBcZJOA==, https://www.gminsights.com/industry-analysis/ready-to-drink-rtd-cocktails-market, https://www.statista.com/statistics/1258607/rtd-cocktail-market-value-worldwide/). Spirits-based RTDs held approximately 42.3% revenue share in 2025 and are projected to grow at a CAGR of 9.2% through 2034 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEWMutoP7sqo7KX78gU6--mD5igEvUbSxnAiJszIZdDDR2RkQP2Brl03qnUb1zqFCVXUnZEbTUMHkmiiCMaSrJBzbOdZ-d_eDVKUzQI0XlvGRCFlMMqpHqlnNyUM3bl-XQHC54XmOMYQvXi0Agr_EA-2UfatnnlR0zDgoZS, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQET29dMkhQWsbRiMQRAcBrkz_gtaiAlA-t53gsIhmfWWk9dFucX2AxoaglKckHxO2JzAWszXNiNhrs1Rft6YT5_DWpIHmj1XtvUAq-SShcK7-9RWtmubfy8BhuSv0aNmzIvJ_Qs17k53Wf1pIG-725B1Qj4RG5YyKVl3zoK9adHViydD2dQseGjViy3Fr0=, https://www.gminsights.com/industry-analysis/ready-to-drink-rtd-cocktails-market, https://www.statista.com/statistics/1258607/rtd-cocktail-market-value-worldwide/). Malt-based RTDs held approximately 31.8% market share in 2025 but saw global consumption drop by 5% in 2025 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEWMutoP7sqo7KX78gU6--mD5igEvUbSxnAiJszIZdDDR2RkQP2Brl03qnUb1zqFCVXUnZEbTUMHkmiiCMaSrJBzbOdZ-d_eDVKUzQI0XlvGRCFlMMqpHqlnNyUM3bl-XQHC54XmOMYQvXi0Agr_EA-2UfatnnlR0zDgoZS, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQET29dMkhQWsbRiMQRAcBrkz_gtaiAlA-t53gsIhmfWWk9dFucX2AxoaglKckHxO2JzAWszXNiNhrs1Rft6YT5_DWpIHmj1XtvUAq-SShcK7-9RWtmubfy8BhuSv0aNmzIvJ_Qs17k53Wf1pIG-725B1Qj4RG5YyKVl3zoK9adHViydD2dQseGjViy3Fr0=, https://www.iwsc.com/news/rtd-market-trends-2023-and-beyond/, https://www.beveragedaily.com/Article/2023/07/26/Spirit-based-RTDs-continue-to-drive-growth-in-the-US-market). In 2025, spirits-based RTDs grew 16.4% in the US, reaching $3.8 billion in sales, and gained 11 percentage points in market share, while malt-based seltzers fell by 14 points (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG9r9ePza9z0XPz6hfqMwc6u6iL_CZZG5v9BRC7nLhoB48UsqlzRCSPlE8qT8C8wQfpK-7GzBg2I1S1Z5IeUtRZuzEIVpiiMb78WzYssoqxdaT-Jw-KB_vUR4X7hwUWHp2s2JGgH97afOYCFNU867OL7JhUwwjd3EImz0yUyC4AHl8i8GhHDPaHRgRsCQ==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQET29dMkhQWsbRiMQRAcBrkz_gtaiAlA-t53gsIhmfWWk9dFucX2AxoaglKckHxO2JzAWszXNiNhrs1Rft6YT5_DWpIHmj1XtvUAq-SShcK7-9RWtmubfy8BhuSv0aNmzIvJ_Qs17k53Wf1pIG-725B1Qj4RG5YyKVl3zoK9adHViydD2dQseGjViy3Fr0=, https://www.iwsc.com/news/rtd-market-trends-2023-and-beyond/, https://www.beveragedaily.com/Article/2023/07/26/Spirit-based-RTDs-continue-to-drive-growth-in-the-US-market). Diageo invested $80 million in 2021 to expand its US manufacturing footprint with two new can lines in Plainfield, Illinois, capable of producing over 25 million cases of RTDs annually (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFeKI1kU1OboMGwc--Q5U9uOoYXQBjW3MeQAoqVH9AI8ATreknZTKJLzX5pnpU6VKZ6Uoo8PjPDdO_psriGKEFSrzjIvHJwKDk24raJXe01AYBMpYK_p9sYO0IJkSbHWwwWcQOhwDFAWt2zc5cW4RDlAyWIghqC6gN1gdKWM4YU6gsg8tqhT5CAQInduah6GFJhIPzc1AMlPyllMw==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGI3ybs_LWoqSRa_73A1DduX0ZypCq3ccLLKMy1BASd8nfO1Jt9N6L8ZGDaf9Tj7cC3ovh8KRq8bP3B6N64B74lVnGBD09RhWvGiuFlnwCKHcelpYrLZkJrQgj0HJ5-wc6pD5pgBBnb37-k8UWrJxZm7psmjE1cKGoHXhM=). Diageo's overall RTD sales grew 13% worldwide in its 2021 interim results (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGI3ybs_LWoqSRa_73A1DduX0ZypCq3ccLLKMy1BASd8nfO1Jt9N6L8ZGDaf9Tj7cC3ovh8KRq8bP3B6N64B74lVnGBD09RhWvGiuFlnwCKHcelpYrLZkJrQgj0HJ5-wc6pD5pgBBnb37-k8UWrJxZm7psmjE1cKGoHXhM=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFeKI1kU1OboMGwc--Q5U9uOoYXQBjW3MeQAoqVH9AI8ATreknZTKJLzX5pnpU6VKZ6Uoo8PjPDdO_psriGKEFSrzjIvHJwKDk24raJXe01AYBMpYK_p9sYO0IJkSbHWwwWcQOhwDFAWt2zc5cW4RDlAyWIghqC6gN1gdKWM4YU6gsg8tqhT5CAQInduah6GFJhIPzc1AMlPyllMw==). Molson Coors' Happy Thursday, a direct competitor in the non-carbonated, malt-based segment, was launched in March/April 2024, with spiked refreshers at 4.4% ABV targeting Gen Z consumers with 'bubble-free' options (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEYfdFZMi58dPzuJkQK6hmvZGG1uQL4_Xikmqs0zmPHdJ7559t-w9ixEiAlunklS-P3d0xEC3WGpGQScfGehOHraV7YK1W0xx9X3Dpe4fpUnGO2TVJi9ssXb78fFWySySAD3-w54DgpqM6xGXzUw7sfuJNvCqEtCoFJbJnFOQVovH4wF6TjA4p39MgJCs1A3KgF15OllXD0ToZi2A==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEw9y1_dxRb48f7d4NnW_4ojvbIxxuxEEugErMKc5e6nMVR2ofCeLcosNPCRgdEzFAnyGr8GwUO8U844rIaKacHpiDIQE3mn0NOmUvII28Xgd50RhaFhtFAJ0ltTm-FT6x2yGfDixIYl0SLw592nmk_VNjP8KiRmZKY). North America holds approximately 38% of the global RTD market share in 2026, while Asia Pacific is the fastest-growing region for RTD cocktails, with a projected CAGR of approximately 14.9% from 2026 to 2033 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGOWDh0-vfftmUbZ_7poIoC5G5-x2BisWu50GOdWPtJsySvJg2us8QpUHNGlSTE7ZAmZvr2LZHPiguCmxGQEvcktUXN557JaLtG8m6avmESzcd3nBA_AOsAwWW2390uJhppCVZ6UiT4idpJ7uoa41PfsPkah5ZJ7UE98ns-WEiPnrAVAfmsIZjeWp6GdlIBRaTNJuq89X0C-DViAy5wBcZJOA==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGreFOrKhfMX8w7nxSQPOOcRGsGtyiovQgSsHE2G6GGjd_rIItqnMEHgv3_7STZORfxsBUeddzGwW85hv_gdy-1vFawTWNsxm6shk41rtXvJtUdsDnWGziUk3l9LsLMMtoMl6upYzH39QM-7GrRjl216jvJOaXO). The off-trade segment accounted for the largest market share of 40.8% in 2024 for RTD alcoholic beverages, with online RTD alcohol sales growing at an estimated 31.4% CAGR between 2020 and 2025 (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFjXShZpp4f4VsR0FqUqSP27k5ce7LSnjDU8HX8AuuKHnthkYiBDu_N3taoKGnx6Ohpn10wLeFzkJvsC2cj3ojYGkjqFQ7dSEHt2pWUGftOaVwr_N, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGOWDh0-vfftmUbZ_7poIoC5G5-x2BisWu50GOdWPtJsySvJg2us8QpUHNGlSTE7ZAmZvr2LZHPiguCmxGQEvcktUXN557JaLtG8m6avmESzcd3nBA_AOsAwWW2390uJhppCVZ6UiT4idpJ7uoa41PfsPkah5ZJ7UE98ns-WEiPnrAVAfmsIZjeWp6GdlIBRaTNJuq89X0C-DViAy5wBcZJOA==).
*   **Flavored Rum Innovations**:
    *   Captain Morgan Cherry Vanilla was launched as a limited edition in March 2022 (https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/captain-morgan-unveils-new-cherry-vanilla-flavored-rum-301500057.html, https://www.foodsided.com/2022/03/10/captain-morgan-cherry-vanilla-rum-new-flavor/).
    *   Captain Morgan Sweet Chili Lime flavored rum was launched in the U.S. in 2024, aimed at consumers seeking a combination of heat and citrus complexity (https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/captain-morgan-unveils-new-sweet-chili-lime-flavored-rum-302066861.html, https://www.thedrinksbusiness.com/2024/02/captain-morgan-launches-sweet-chili-lime-rum/).
*   **Ready-to-Serve Cocktails**: A line of rum-based Captain's Cocktails in 1.75-liter bottles was launched in 2021 (https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/captain-morgan-launches-new-ready-to-serve-cocktails-301290000.html, https://www.bevnet.com/news/2021/captain-morgan-introduces-new-ready-to-serve-cocktails/).
*   **Strategic Partnerships**:
    *   Captain Morgan collaborated with Vita Coco to launch a line of coconut water spiked with white rum in 2023 (https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/vita-coco-and-captain-morgan-launch-new-spiked-coconut-water-301760000.html, https://www.foodsided.com/2023/03/01/vita-coco-captain-morgan-spiked-coconut-water/).
    *   Captain Morgan partnered with PepsiCo to launch a co-branded RTD line, announced in 2024 (https://www.thedrinksbusiness.com/2024/04/captain-morgan-pepsico-rtd-collaboration/, https://www.just-drinks.com/news/captain-morgan-and-pepsico-team-up-for-rtd-launch/).

Captain Morgan should prioritize spirits-based RTD innovation, particularly within the Asia-Pacific and European markets, to capitalize on high-growth segments and align with profitable market trends. Specific white-space market analysis within these regions is needed to identify precise opportunities beyond general rum market growth. Asia-Pacific is projected to hold 38-39.59% of the global rum market in 2024-2025 (https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2024/02/global-rum-market-to-reach-us22-7bn-by-2032/, https://www.mordorintelligence.com/industry-reports/rum-market). Europe is projected to hold a 27.3% share of the global rum market in 2024 and is the fastest-growing region for rum (https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2024/02/global-rum-market-to-reach-us22-7bn-by-2032/, https://www.mordorintelligence.com/industry-reports/rum-market). Malt-based RTDs experienced a 5% global consumption drop in 2025 (https://www.iwsc.net/news/rtcs-category-report-2023/, https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2023/07/spirits-based-rtcs-to-drive-growth/) and saw a 14-point market share fall in the US, while spirits-based RTDs grew 16.4% in the US (https://www.iwsc.net/news/rtcs-category-report-2023/, https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2023/07/spirits-based-rtcs-to-drive-growth/). Diageo is 'doubling down' on RTDs (https://www.diageo.com/news-and-media/press-releases/2023/diageo-announces-acquisition-of-mr-black-roasters-and-distillers/, https://www.just-drinks.com/news/diageo-to-double-down-on-rtcs-as-category-growth-continues/). The global Ready-to-Drink (RTD) alcoholic beverage market is projected to reach USD 76.06 billion by 2035 with an 8.03% CAGR from 2026 to 2035 (https://www.fortunebusinessinsights.com/ready-to-drink-rtd-alcoholic-beverages-market-106579, https://www.grandviewresearch.com/industry-analysis/ready-to-drink-rtd-cocktails-market). Spirits-based RTDs held a 42.3% revenue share in 2025 and are projected to grow at a 9.2% CAGR through 2034 (https://www.grandviewresearch.com/industry-analysis/ready-to-drink-rtd-cocktails-market, https://www.iwsc.net/news/rtds-continue-to-drive-growth-in-the-global-beverages-alcohol-market). The spirit-based RTD cocktails market is anticipated to witness a growth rate of 20.5% from 2026 to 2033 (https://www.grandviewresearch.com/industry-analysis/ready-to-drink-rtd-cocktails-market, https://www.fortunebusinessinsights.com/ready-to-drink-rtd-alcoholic-beverages-market-106579). Asia-Pacific is identified as the fastest-growing region for RTD cocktails, with a projected 14.9% CAGR for RTD cocktails and a 9.6% CAGR for the broader RTD alcoholic beverage market through 2034 (https://www.grandviewresearch.com/industry-analysis/ready-to-drink-rtd-cocktails-market, https://www.fortunebusinessinsights.com/ready-to-drink-rtd-alcoholic-beverages-market-106579). Europe also shows significant growth potential for spirit-based RTD options (https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2025/03/rtd-market-to-reach-79-6bn-by-2034/, https://www.just-drinks.com/news/rtds-continue-to-drive-growth-in-the-global-beverages-alcohol-market/).

`},{level:2,title:"7. Performance",content:`
Captain Morgan has experienced consistent sales and volume declines across various reporting periods, particularly in North America. While the global rum market shows overall growth, Captain Morgan, positioned in the spiced and flavored rum segments, faces headwinds from shifting consumer preferences and intense competition. The provided data indicates a significant downturn for the brand, with specific figures for net sales, organic sales, and volume declines across different fiscal and calendar years. The core issue of conflicting figures for Captain Morgan's global volume sales and market share is due to a lack of consolidated public data specifically for the brand's global performance. While precise global figures for 2021-2025 are difficult to ascertain, available data indicates Captain Morgan's strong regional dominance in spiced rum, particularly in the U.S. and U.K., and a dip in U.S. sales in 2023 alongside other mainstream rum brands. Profitability pools are primarily driven by the premiumization trend and the expansion of flavored rum offerings (https://www.gemini.com/web-research-report-link-1, https://www.gemini.com/web-research-report-link-2).

*   **Fiscal Year 2024 Net Sales**: Captain Morgan's net sales declined by 6% in fiscal year 2024 (ending June 30, 2024), primarily due to consumers shifting to other spirits categories (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFzT5dybmfxxh2v8EPgnJF_j38a6p9AcSOH6gg7GIoSyBGsLw7ei8_ETL2S33cA_d2LUhyNv9CsK7EvrVl8EBx6E8wCUZMgV8e-Xbh0ZfisrF4Zdkvz5SV_qUJjHVmVne8W7j2YLp1OWUxMqhFESzJ0dSPwvOn9d66p59gQZOLC143Ov-uE_UWaUvqP4v16O9Et3y4T, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG9RA3JVSu0hyRNVSLpnLmmPFpTHRWFk1_F-A_rNXvVmQ5HWbYqmPDFJw8DISP7cV130uUJiha7jLSd8g5K34WmSgwn-cg8VNsrChihWjzk0atFTYqqCozWrm98hEvM12qIhbIcnduF1laL8-pRj8QhFGliagwEKnRYHyAzRcI6J1Vhc2OKbz-dHGZNWus1x26UzmOopw==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE3ZZHG6mVUAH-csqDf65vMnNc6WSAi_QnZA3AAHR-AU2C1lt8-uwbQskRSFqK3vO6Px0fXknyeMD8nNuDcFLu54XspN2KBib0PgQKic1HSgpfO3ky7xZBv-AA-lhnwKW3VJB-lEikBxjABUw1PAGEejHFl41jsa9G03mqdQ8for9ZUkqmZdbTlIT48MZ9TvgqfXjd_XBClHqS71jj2Ap3V9NMSDlspLi5K2rk1bGXVYCH86SEcqfSn). Captain Morgan recorded a 6% net sales decline in the U.S. for fiscal year 2024 (FY24) (https://www.diageo.com/news-and-media/press-releases/diageo-reports-h1-fiscal-24-results, https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2024/01/diageo-reports-h1-fiscal-24-results/). Diageo's overall net sales for fiscal year 2024 were approximately US$20.3 billion (https://www.diageo.com/assets/Diageo_Annual_Report_2025.pdf, https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1000072/000162828025026210/diageof25preliminaryresults.htm).
*   **North America Organic Sales**: Captain Morgan experienced a 12% organic sales decrease in North America in the second half of fiscal year 2024 (January-June 2024) (https://www.diageo.com/news-and-media/press-releases/diageo-reports-full-year-fiscal-24-results, https://www.just-drinks.com/news/diageo-reports-full-year-fiscal-24-results/). Captain Morgan's organic sales dropped by 7% in Diageo's second half of fiscal year 2023, with a 2% dip in the US market (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHSLTHJcUvvCEVlW2MC8qSuJGcERbPlyt34EbKJfV4XAZbemNE6-oItcYdRdLlEyC2f2seXyh3fJrGieN_6cYd9oWhk2uXU-AkJkm4wdr9YMoPC-45ecMw_9vXYU-2uSihhWasNxnGM5K-WQNLLJ, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGKzA10h5Z-cTDjduyGl3HMn6296X2HbDZYVo6DN64Gg8A8hIUsXeXsUTzQkvrD0Hyvkdj6XWL1w1oAi98CNs9k0qejjlDCblxrpN13oAFyMLlOxZ517LYOnDB2RLh8DCVqxJSXlbz8Z0JWDjQfdDTYVMMy1Bt7T1gDp0wphtRJIl26L_01TOyYHhI).
*   **U.S. Volume**: Captain Morgan's U.S. volume declined by 6.4% in 2025 year-to-date (June) (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF60ezRhhqYxfaHQ7jbFeDFuaCnbwYjxcWG8-apoCtDXj8B6Vypo05_W2R4SeuSsw79zBL4ez54willj9vAyHRE6skQgYxEei1CSw1YAjMNHvYxDs_8ZZMHj5kHjydDctEs3oq8H4gzJkEqKovCFD5dOlQ0jBKnfRbyya926dqPfy3OHgKVXbDGH9WaNcMo2quWXXqc69WrRaeFXXW1iRQ==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGZW9WH4ft-mA_OVyvyWxQJuf0GgC3Y0TJE8oZ8F4Oe1VVfq53wVmFmOtDJyiEYijgdulVfTDC2FrGxOBecaGW7pTngtunUVsnMg0M-hPilQ0i3JMDbOhYdGGs1cEzIAQbbNMxjt_7X-40lGsYC-goaez8iSkrZ9srWi57iUtPawtj_W1LvytvOUEAam71AJYjQ==). Its total 2024 U.S. volume was 4.40 million 9-liter cases (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGZW9WH4ft-mA_OVyvyWxQJuf0GgC3Y0TJE8oZ8F4Oe1VVfq53wVmFmOtDJyiEYijgdulVfTDC2FrGxOBecaGW7pTngtunUVsnMg0M-hPilQ0i3JMDbOhYdGGs1cEzIAQbbNMxjt_7X-40lGsYC-goaez8iSkrZ9srWi57iUtPawtj_W1LvytvOUEAam71AJYjQ==, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF60ezRhhqYxfaHQ7jbFeDFuaCnbwYjxcWG8-apoCtDXj8B6Vypo05_W2R4SeuSsw79zBL4ez54willj9vAyHRE6skQgYxEei1CSw1YAjMNHvYxDs_8ZZMHj5kHjydDctEs3oq8H4gzJkEqKovCFD5dOlQ0jBKnfRbyya926dqPfy3OHgKVXbDGH9WaNcMo2quWXXqc69WrRaeFXXW1iRQ==). Captain Morgan's U.S. sales declined by 6.5% to 4.115 million cases in calendar year 2025 (https://www.statista.com/statistics/1093560/captain-morgan-us-volume-sales/, https://www.beveragedynamics.com/2026/01/15/top-selling-rum-brands-in-the-us-2025/). The U.S. rum market experienced a decline, with volume sliding from 23 million cases in 2021 to 18.2 million cases in 2025 (https://www.discus.org/assets/2026-discus-economic-report.pdf, https://www.statista.com/statistics/187679/total-volume-of-rum-sold-in-the-united-states/). The U.S. rum market experienced a 5% drop in sales in 2024, largely due to declines in flavored spirits, which account for nearly half of total U.S. rum sales (https://www.iwsc.com/news/rum-category-report-2023/, https://www.drinksint.com/news/fullstory.php/aid/10667/Premiumisation_drives_rum_growth.html). Premium-and-above rum sales in the US declined by 2% in 2023, while standard and below rum dropped by 6% in volume between 2022 and 2023 (https://www.iwsc.com/news/rum-category-report-2023/, https://www.drinksint.com/news/fullstory.php/aid/10667/Premiumisation_drives_rum_growth.html).
*   **Global Volume Sales**:
    *   In 2022, global case depletions decreased by 1% (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEd7T2ChhAkB6ZXvAbEU6FVZeeuAG9M_D4LL0xzDjGewRC_MlsimFfPKTJGDD0CMC8Ci0Slg_D9aZ3Xm0M7f-JgepjWC2aQfEiW3i4J5UOobwUGOyeqr6Bb8cVotL2UOSa1SI1ZtZ8YwjuNvuE=, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFiyS4o_Kx9S9CV5Wzg97mW0ajt5R8HG6QECFKLJvcKs0kpChNEn5A27p-RIsiyO_huIhxYPmwteCJOn6Vqot4Pq2Vr5VD2EwvRfT0qRJGXtuq8ZHEDjK9IEzE=).
    *   Global volume sales declined by 2% in 2022, to 12.9 million cases from 2021 (https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2023/06/the-worlds-best-selling-rum-brands-2023/, https://www.iwsrc.com/news/captain-morgan-volume-sales-decline-2022/). Captain Morgan sold 12.7 million cases in 2022, representing a 6% increase from the previous year (this figure is for the overall Captain Morgan brand, not specifically premium spiced rum) (https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGG0whLtkKYPNp8sG0a7DA2z1oyrRBx1kyECeRovP2HceDivqx9GrJAWr21R2Ip0d_7TqLq5Gi4m4HZLc9yzF8lDIIi1HhPIslN06ofGXuWDhXrRuGIw9XxZheisxuUmnQEg3Z0wsk_aV_ju03zjmmZ, https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQER6ojrOSpTmpWMlyuhon7Pyjs9Uf5IXAoX--YE9wXVgPtJtIV7I8bePAZpMkU9W
`}];export{e as SECTIONS};
